n Accessuhttps://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_abf2funrestricted online access2star  aDie für die moderne chinesische Geschichte charakteristische Verbindung von Kultur und Politik gewinnt in der Bewegung des 4. Mai 1919 ihren ersten prägnanten Ausdruck. Die Beiträge des vorliegenden Bandes blicken in unterschiedlichen Perspektiven auf den chinesisch-deutschen Ideenaustausch, der die jene Bewegung kennzeichnende Kontroverse zwischen chinesischer Überlieferung und westlicher Moderne begleitete und nicht selten inspirierte.  aThe union of culture and politics that is so characteristic of modern Chinese history gained its first concise expression in the May Fourth Movement of 1919. The essays in this edited volume examine the exchange of ideas between China and Germany from various perspectives, illuminating how the clash between Chinese tradition and Western modernity accompanied and often inspired the movement.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4a4. Mai 1919. 4aChinesisch-deutscher Dialog. 4aKultur und Revolution in China. 4aModernisierungsprozesse im 20. Jahrhundert. 7aHISTORY / Asia / China.2bisacsh  a20th century modernization processes.  aChinese-German dialogue.  aMay Fourth Movement.  aculture and revolution in China.1 aBauerkämper, Arnd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBo, Fang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChaoran, Huang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeger, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHille, Almut, econtributor.4ctb4https://